issue.title: DataSet method "segmentation_labels" from dataset.py returning empty list.
issue.body:
The method [_segmentation_labels_] from the class [DataSet](https://github.com/mapillary/OpenSfM/blob/c6b5acef9376a75b87414d900c258ef876a6413a/opensfm/dataset.py#L27) should return all the unique classes labels contained in the segmentation masks. Instead, it return an empty list which is useless considering that it is misleading. It should be defined according to the segmentations folder linked to the dataset object (check if there is segmentations and check for unique values contained inside of each image) and add each unique class value inside a set.

```python
def segmentation_labels(self) -> List[Any]:
        return []
```
It should at least raise an error if there is no segmentations linked to the object.

comment.body: @Pikauba I don't think the _segmentation_labels()_ function is used anymore, I thought that subclasses will use it to **actually** write logic for the code but I checked and it is called once in feature_processing.py. The method might have been deprecated or something. If you look at _load_segmentation_labels_ in dense.py, that function makes a lot of sense just like in features.py,  `segmentation_labels=np.array(semantic.labels).astype(str)`
